trans-unit.source: Looking to upgrade from a previous version of Visual Studio?
trans-unit.target: Looking to upgrade from a previous version of Visual Studio?

trans-unit.source: Visual Studio 2017 offers the latest C# support, is faster than ever, and makes you more productive.
trans-unit.target: Visual Studio 2017 offers the latest C# support, is faster than ever, and makes you more productive.

trans-unit.source: Install Visual Studio 2017 side-by-side with your current version to try it out!
trans-unit.target: Install Visual Studio 2017 side-by-side with your current version to try it out!

trans-unit.source: Visual Studio 2017 supports the latest advancements in C# 7.3 which focus on performance and productivity.
trans-unit.target: Visual Studio 2017 supports the latest advancements in C# 7.3 which focus on performance and productivity.

trans-unit.source: Features like tuples, pattern-matching, and out var from C# 7.0 will help you work with data and make your code more readable, while 7.3 brings you improvements in ref variables, Span, Enum constraints, and more.
trans-unit.target: Features like tuples, pattern-matching, and out var from C# 7.0 will help you work with data and make your code more readable, while 7.3 brings you improvements in ref variables, Span, Enum constraints, and more.

trans-unit.source: Learn more about C# 7.3 support
trans-unit.target: Learn more about C# 7.3 support

trans-unit.source: With Visual Studio 2017, solutions load anywhere from 35% faster up to twice as fast as in Visual Studio 2015.
trans-unit.target: With Visual Studio 2017, solutions load anywhere from 35% faster up to twice as fast as in Visual Studio 2015.

trans-unit.source: The installation process is also faster and more lightweight, thanks to a modular install experience that lets you pick only what you need.
trans-unit.target: The installation process is also faster and more lightweight, thanks to a modular install experience that lets you pick only what you need.

trans-unit.source: Learn more about solution load performance
trans-unit.target: Learn more about solution load performance

trans-unit.source: With each release of Visual Studio 2017 come new refactoring capabilities, driven by your user feedback.
trans-unit.target: With each release of Visual Studio 2017 come new refactoring capabilities, driven by your user feedback.

trans-unit.source: Add null-check, invert if-statement, remove unused variable, and toggle between ‘var’ and the explicit type are just a few of the new features added.
trans-unit.target: Add null-check, invert if-statement, remove unused variable, and toggle between ‘var’ and the explicit type are just a few of the new features added.

trans-unit.source: Learn more about refactoring capabilities
trans-unit.target: Learn more about refactoring capabilities

trans-unit.source: The Visual Studio 2017 debugger allows you to diagnose issues faster with key new features like Run To Click, which enables you to run the debugger to a specific line of code.
trans-unit.target: The Visual Studio 2017 debugger allows you to diagnose issues faster with key new features like Run To Click, which enables you to run the debugger to a specific line of code.

trans-unit.source: IntelliTrace step-back enables Visual Studio Enterprise users to go back to a previous breakpoint or step and view the application in the state it was in at that time.
trans-unit.target: IntelliTrace step-back enables Visual Studio Enterprise users to go back to a previous breakpoint or step and view the application in the state it was in at that time.

trans-unit.source: Learn more about IntelliTrace step-back
trans-unit.target: Learn more about IntelliTrace step-back

trans-unit.source: The unit testing experience across multiple frameworks has also been improved in Visual Studio 2017, with Test Explorer performance enhancements, a hierarchy view of tests, and Live Unit Testing for Visual Studio Enterprise users, giving you instant feedback on which tests are impacted by code changes.
trans-unit.target: The unit testing experience across multiple frameworks has also been improved in Visual Studio 2017, with Test Explorer performance enhancements, a hierarchy view of tests, and Live Unit Testing for Visual Studio Enterprise users, giving you instant feedback on which tests are impacted by code changes.

trans-unit.source: Learn more about Live Unit Testing
trans-unit.target: Learn more about Live Unit Testing

trans-unit.source: 1. Download and start the Visual Studio Installer.
trans-unit.target: 1. Download and start the Visual Studio Installer.

trans-unit.source: Tab Down to Select a Version of Visual Studio
trans-unit.target: Tab Down to Select a Version of Visual Studio

trans-unit.source: Choose the workloads that align best to the type of development that you do.
trans-unit.target: Choose the workloads that align best to the type of development that you do.

trans-unit.source: We recommend you add no more than 3-4 workloads, as you can always come back to the Visual Studio Installer at any time to add more.
trans-unit.target: We recommend you add no more than 3-4 workloads, as you can always come back to the Visual Studio Installer at any time to add more.

trans-unit.source: 3. Install Visual Studio 2017 side-by-side with your current version.
trans-unit.target: 3. Install Visual Studio 2017 side-by-side with your current version.

trans-unit.source: 4. Check out the Visual Studio 2017 C# productivity guide for tips on how to become more productive than ever.
trans-unit.target: 4. Check out the Visual Studio 2017 C# productivity guide for tips on how to become more productive than ever.
